---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Education - Fragrant Signatures"
  description="Educational programs and courses for creating natural perfumes - School of Natural Perfumery Fragrant Signatures"
  currentPath="/en/education"
  lang="en"
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-botanical-50 via-white to-nature-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16 max-w-6xl">
      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <div class="mb-8">
          <img 
            src="/images/fw-logo-red.png" 
            alt="Fragrant Signatures Logo"
            class="mx-auto max-w-md h-auto"
          />
        </div>
        
        <!-- Stylized Divider -->
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-8">
          <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-botanical-300 to-transparent"></div>
          <div class="mx-4 w-2 h-2 bg-botanical-500 rounded-full"></div>
          <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-botanical-300 to-transparent"></div>
        </div>
        
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8">
          Education
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-botanical-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Discover the world of natural perfumes through our educational programs
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Spare Forms -->
      <div class="mb-12 flex justify-center">
        <a
          href="/documents/Rezervni obrasci_MP_ENG.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="group inline-flex flex-col items-center gap-1 px-10 py-5 bg-botanical-800 hover:bg-botanical-700 text-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 transform hover:-translate-y-0.5"
        >
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-botanical-300 group-hover:text-botanical-200 transition-colors">Spare Forms</span>
          <span class="flex items-center gap-2 text-base font-bold">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 16v1a3 3 0 003 3h10a3 3 0 003-3v-1m-4-4l-4 4m0 0l-4-4m4 4V4" />
            </svg>
            Download PDF
          </span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="space-y-12">

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8 text-center">Fragrant Signatures – School of Natural Perfumery</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-ink-800 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
            <p>
              Some research results say that when choosing perfumes, we prefer those that fit well with <a href="https://academic.oup.com/beheco/article-abstract/12/2/140/239863?redirectedFrom=fulltext&login=false" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-botanical-600 hover:text-botanical-800 underline font-medium transition-colors duration-300">the natural scent of our bodies</a> and harmoniously complete it, thus emphasizing our biological signal.
            </p>
            <p>
              If you want to wear a perfume that will cooperate well with your body chemistry, the task of its creation can be best performed by you, your nose and your brain. The self-created natural perfume is an item well worth including into one's personal well-being toolbox.
            </p>
            <p>
              Would you like to learn how to create such a perfume? If so, you've come to the right place. The goal of Fragrant Signatures – School of Natural Perfumery is to provide you with tools to immerse yourself in the world of natural fragrant materials and learn how to create your own natural perfumes. People wore such perfumes till the end of the 19th century, when they became too expensive and too complicated to produce, so they were replaced by synthetic fragrances.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-botanical-800 bg-gradient-to-r from-botanical-50 to-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-accent-500">
              You are invited to join the education.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Study Topics & Target Groups -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-6">Study Topics</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-ink-800">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>What is natural perfume</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Short history of using natural fragrant materials</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Materials used in natural perfumery</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Scent profiles and classifications of fragrant materials</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Notes and accords</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Skin chemistry and the effect of scent on emotions</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Different forms of perfumes</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Different creation methods</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Building bases</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Safety, Ecology, Sustainability</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Guidelines for further education</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-6">Target Groups</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-ink-800">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Beginners or professionals interested in natural perfumery.</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Aromatherapists who want their blends to be as well adjusted to their clients' individual needs as possible.</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Everyone who wants to sharpen their ability to perceive, recognize and discriminate scents.</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Formulators of natural cosmetics who want to improve the scent of their products.</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Gourmet enthusiasts, sommeliers, winemakers and chefs, because the senses of taste and smell are closely related.</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>All kinds of therapists who want to support their work with an adequate scent background.</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Meditation, yoga and mindfulness practitioners.</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">•</span>Everyone who loves natural scents and wants to get closer to themselves through creative work.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Modules overview -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-botanical-50 to-nature-50 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-6 text-center">Education consists of two modules</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">MODULE 1</h4>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm">Basic course in creating natural perfumes</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">MODULE 2</h4>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm">Advanced course for perfecting the art</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- MODULE 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8 text-center">Module 1</h3>

          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-ink-800 space-y-3">
              <p>Programme is divided into six sessions, including an introductory session, followed by four weekends of practice (one per month) and a follow-up session.</p>
              <p>After each weekend of practice, students are given tasks that they should master by the next meeting.</p>
              <p>Prior to the follow-up session students have to complete a final assignment.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">Introductory Meeting (2–3 hours)</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Getting to know each other</li>
                  <li>• Agreement on working methods</li>
                  <li>• Presentation of the contents of the work kit</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-nature-800 mb-3">First Weekend</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Introduction</li>
                  <li>• Fragrant Materials</li>
                  <li>• Sourcing, Selecting and Storing Fragrant Materials</li>
                  <li>• Working with Fragrant Materials</li>
                  <li>• How to Evaluate Scents</li>
                  <li>• Notes in Perfumery</li>
                  <li>• Base Notes Evaluation</li>
                  <li>• Discussion: Impressions and Personal Preferences</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Second Weekend</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Classification by Scent Groups</li>
                  <li>• Accords</li>
                  <li>• Evaluation of Middle Notes</li>
                  <li>• Discussion: Impressions and Personal Preferences</li>
                  <li>• Perfume Formulation Method by Jean Carles</li>
                  <li>• Base Accord Creation</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">Third Weekend</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Discussion: Experience of Creating the Base Accord / Olfactory Impression</li>
                  <li>• Skin Chemistry</li>
                  <li>• Perfume Evolution</li>
                  <li>• Top Notes Evaluation</li>
                  <li>• Creating a Middle Accord</li>
                  <li>• First Impressions of the Middle Accord</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-nature-800 mb-3">Fourth Weekend</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Discussion: Experience of Creating the Top Accord / Olfactory Impression</li>
                  <li>• Filling in the Perfume Formula Form</li>
                  <li>• Balancing Accords – Trials and Selection</li>
                  <li>• Perfume Creation</li>
                  <li>• Perfumes' Classification by Concentration</li>
                  <li>• On Possible post festum Interventions</li>
                  <li>• Questions and Concluding Discussion</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Follow-up Meeting</h5>
                <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm mb-2">Approx. 1.5 months later, after the period of perfumes' maturation.</p>
                <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Before this meeting, a final assignment should be handed in:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-ink-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  <li>1. a paper on the given topic</li>
                  <li>2. completed perfume evaluation form</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm font-semibold mb-2">The content of the meeting:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Discussion about the creative process carried out</li>
                  <li>• Guidelines for further work</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-botanical-50 to-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
              <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Details about the Education</h5>
              <div class="space-y-3 text-ink-800 text-sm">
                <p>• Before the start of the education, each student will receive a starter kit. It consists of 21 fragrant materials for the perfumer's palette, and several useful items that facilitate the work at home.</p>
                <p>• It is necessary to purchase the manual Fragrant Signatures. You can order it <a href="/en/order/" class="text-botanical-600 hover:text-botanical-800 underline font-medium transition-colors duration-300">here</a>.</p>
                <p>• Everyone should also prepare 15 (10 ml) amber glass bottles with pipettes / caps, small labels, a sufficient amount of blotters, and a thick notebook for recording olfactory impressions, thoughts, ideas...</p>
                <p>• Classes are usually held on Saturdays and Sundays from 4:00 PM to 7:30 PM Central European Time. (During the introductory meeting, we can adjust the schedule to suit everyone.)</p>
                <p>• The entire education is held interactively, without prerecorded videos, in real time and with the constant support of the mentor. This is why, despite the online form, the education is still very personal and enables the formation of close contact within the group. To acquire this type of knowledge, working in a group is of crucial importance, because a lot is learned by listening to the impressions and opinions of other participants (a-ha moments!), and discussing them.</p>
                <p>• The created perfume is unique, and represents your personal, specific fragrant signature. Its formulation was influenced by your physical, mental, psychological and spiritual needs, which shape each person's olfactory preferences. You can wear it as your only and forever perfume that will accompany you at every step and in all life situations. Or you can modify it over time and adapt it to your changing needs. And, of course, you can create a lot of other perfumes whenever you decide so, as this education prepares you to that.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-botanical-200">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Education includes:</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Working in a small group and in real time</li>
                  <li>• Starter kit: carefully chosen fragrant materials and equipment</li>
                  <li>• Interactivity and tasks for individual work at home</li>
                  <li>• Careful mentoring throughout the entire perfume making process</li>
                  <li>• Certificate of completion</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-botanical-200">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Details:</h5>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> Live online: 38 teaching hours. Individual work at home: minimum 30 hours.</p>
                  <p><strong>Language:</strong> English</p>
                  <p><strong>Location:</strong> Online event via ZOOM</p>
                  <p><strong>Price:</strong> 900,00 EUR</p>
                  <p><strong>Group size:</strong> maximum 10 people</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl text-sm text-ink-800">
              To ensure the quality of work, a maximum of 10 people can be accepted to the group. When places are taken, you will be put on the waiting list, just in case a place becomes available at the last minute. Thank you for your understanding!
            </div>

            <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl text-center">
              <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Information and Registration:</h5>
              <p class="text-ink-800 font-semibold">+385 91 788 6783</p>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm mt-2">Invitations to enroll are sent on average twice a year, and training takes place when a group of interested parties is formed.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl text-sm text-ink-800">
              <strong>Note:</strong> After completing Module 1 participants are trained to create alcohol perfumes and can finish their education at this level.
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-botanical-200 text-center">
              <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-2">Copyright:</h5>
              <p class="text-ink-800">The author of <a href="https://aromaterapija.info/skola-kreiranja-prirodnih-parfema/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-botanical-600 hover:text-botanical-800 underline font-medium transition-colors duration-300">Fragrant Signatures education</a> is Slobodanka Poštić.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- MODULE 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8 text-center">Module 2</h3>

          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-nature-50 to-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl prose prose-lg max-w-none text-ink-800 space-y-4">
              <p>This module is intended for those persistent and curious who want to learn further, improve their art of composing natural perfumes, and refine their creations.</p>
              <p>Those who already have experience in the creation of natural perfumes do not have to pre-complete Module 1, but they will need to demonstrate (during the introductory interview) that they possess the knowledge required for the Module 2 level of education.</p>
              <p class="font-semibold">Note: In order to be able to work with a larger amount of fragrant components, students are expected to have Module 1 palette materials on hand.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-botanical-50 to-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
              <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Details about the Education</h5>
              <div class="space-y-3 text-ink-800 text-sm">
                <p>• Before the start of the education, each student will receive a learning kit. It contains 20 fragrant materials for the perfumer's palette and several useful items that facilitate the work at home. Students will be instructed how to prepare their palettes.</p>
                <p>• Everyone should also prepare 20 (10 ml) amber glass bottles with pipettes / caps, labels, a sufficient amount of blotters, and a thick notebook for recording olfactory impressions, thoughts, ideas…</p>
                <p>• Classes usually take place during the weekend. Working hours are agreed upon at the introductory meeting.</p>
                <p>• The entire education is conducted interactively, without prerecorded videos, in real time and with the constant support of a mentor. That is why, despite the online form, the education is still very personal and allows for close contact within the group. To acquire this kind of knowledge, it is crucial to work in a group, because one learns a lot by listening to the impressions and opinions of other participants (a-ha moments!), and discussing them.</p>
                <p>• During this module you get to know several creation methods and decide on the one that you think will best suit your perfume plan.</p>
                <p>• In the final part, during the follow-up meeting, you can discuss with the mentor your impressions and any dilemmas related to the creation process you went through.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-ink-800 space-y-3">
              <p>Programme is divided into seven sessions, including an introductory meeting, five days of practice (one per month), and a follow-up session. After each day of practice, students are given tasks that they should master by the next meeting. Prior to the follow-up session, students have to complete a final assignment.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">Introductory Meeting</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Getting to know each other</li>
                  <li>• Agreement on the time we will work</li>
                  <li>• Presentation of the contents of the work kit</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-nature-800 mb-3">First Working Day</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Discussion about previous experiences in creating natural perfumes</li>
                  <li>• Evaluation of the first group of fragrant materials in the palette</li>
                  <li>• First impressions, discussion</li>
                  <li>• Theory: work with „difficult" materials, different dilutions, other forms of perfumes</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Second Working Day</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Impressions after getting to know the first group of materials in detail</li>
                  <li>• Evaluation of the next group of fragrant materials</li>
                  <li>• Impressions, discussion</li>
                  <li>• Theory: precise measurement (working with scales)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">Third Working Day</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Discussion after a detailed introduction to the second group of materials</li>
                  <li>• Evaluation of the last group of fragrant materials</li>
                  <li>• Olfactory impressions, discussion</li>
                  <li>• Theory: bases / doppelgangers</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-nature-800 mb-3">Fourth Working Day</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Base creation experience</li>
                  <li>• Theory: different approaches to perfume creation</li>
                  <li>• The decision on the method of creating the perfume (EdT)</li>
                  <li>• Practical work: creating a perfume using the chosen method</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Fifth Working Day</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Creating a natural perfume for another person</li>
                  <li>• Custom perfume making exercise</li>
                  <li>• Discussion about that experience; suggestions</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl md:col-span-2">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">Follow-up Session</h5>
                <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Before this session the participants should submit a final assignment consisting of:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-ink-700 text-sm mb-3">
                  <li>• a paper on the given topic</li>
                  <li>• completed perfume evaluation form</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm font-semibold mb-2">The content of the session:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Discussion about the applied methods of creation and individual reports on the created perfumes.</li>
                  <li>• Suggestions for further work: maintaining creative competence, care for personal ecological footprint, sustainability etc.</li>
                  <li>• Short individual interviews with the mentor.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-botanical-200">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Module 2 includes:</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Work in a small group in real time</li>
                  <li>• A valuable class kit to continue learning about natural perfumery</li>
                  <li>• Interactivity and tasks for individual work at home</li>
                  <li>• Careful mentoring throughout the perfume making process</li>
                  <li>• Certificate of completion</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-botanical-200">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Details:</h5>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> Live online: 26 teaching hours. Individual work at home: minimum 25 hours.</p>
                  <p><strong>Language:</strong> English</p>
                  <p><strong>Location:</strong> Online event via ZOOM</p>
                  <p><strong>Price:</strong> 900,00 EUR</p>
                  <p><strong>Group size:</strong> maximum 8 people</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl text-sm text-ink-800">
              To ensure the quality of work, a maximum of 8 people can be admitted to the group. When places are taken, you will be put on the waiting list, just in case a place becomes available at the last minute. Thank you for your understanding!
            </div>

            <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl text-center">
              <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Information and Registration:</h5>
